The 82 Division of the Nigerian Army has detained one Lance Corporal Ajayi Johnson, suspected to have killed a commercial motorcyclist at Umuokereke Ngwa in the Obingwa Local Government Area of Abia State. Col. Aliyu Yusuf, the division’s Deputy Director, Army Public Relations, said in a statement on Saturday in Enugu, that  the Army had commenced investigations on the killing. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network On August 7, Johnson, said to be on illegal duty, reportedly shot a commercial motorcyclist, Chimaobi Nwaogu, at point blank range, killing him on the spot. “Investigation on the incident revealed that Johnson was one of the soldiers deployed for security duties at Forward Operations Base in Ohanze, but absconded from his duty post to an unknown destination. He was reported to have been involved in a scuffle that led to the shooting and killing of Nwaogu.” Yusuf said that Johnson had been arrested, adding that disciplinary procedures in line with extant military laws had commenced. “If found culpable, he will be dismissed and handed over to the civil police for prosecution. The Nigerian Army deeply regrets this unfortunate incident and prays for the repose of the soul of the deceased. “May the Almighty God strengthen the family of the deceased, his loved ones and the entire residents of Abia State for this irreparable loss,” Yusuf said.